TV personality and actress Connie Ferguson shared a heart-warming message to her late mum Margaret Masilo. The 52-year-old took to Instagram and shared how wonderful her mum was on Monday, 25 July. The actress’ mum passed away in 2013. Connie said it has been nine years since she has been gone but she is grateful for the lessons she taught her while she was still alive. Connie wrote: “The QUEEN of my heart! Always love.” She said the love she has for her will never die. ALSO READ:Connie celebrates Shona on his birthday “I can’t believe it’s 9 years already. I’ll never stop being grateful for all the love and lessons. Love you for eternity Moms,” she wrote. Connie said she must continue resting in eternal peace. Her fans showed her some love, with some of them sharing heartbreaking stories of losing a loved one. Zinhle Mbense said she also misses her mum. “I miss my mom every day and it’s been 15 years but still ngisazama,” she said. “We love you momma,”David Webb said. Dolldiva Matwe said Connie’s mum must continue to rest in eternal peace. A post shared by Connie Ferguson (@connie_ferguson) 